value.title: Live Updates: McConnell backs Trump legal fight in election results
value.excerpt: Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell backed the Trump campaign’s legal challenge of voting results in several battleground states on Monday in his first public comments on the floor since Election Day.

value.title: Ex-Israeli UN Ambassador Danon on what a Biden presidency means for Middle East peace
value.excerpt: Israel's former ambassador to the United Nations Danny Danon provided insight on Monday into what a Biden presidency could mean for Middle East peace.

value.title: Pence on 2020 race: ‘It ain’t over til it’s over...and this AIN’T over!’
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Monday rallied his staff, saying the 2020 presidential race “ain’t over,” as the Trump campaign mounts legal battles in a number of key battleground states where President-elect Joe Biden is leading.

value.title: Mike Huckabee: Trump team must be allowed to examine voting machines, ballots
value.excerpt: President Trump needs to pursue legal action against the 2020 presidential election results due to the state's having suspicious outcomes, Fox News contributor Mike Huckabee said on Monday.

value.title: Biden urges Americans to wear masks: ‘Not a political statement’
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says that wearing a mask remains “the most potent weapon” against the coronavirus, and emphasizes that “a mask is not a political statement.”

value.title: Rep. Van Drew: Trump ripped the band-aid off, changed American politics
value.excerpt: Democrat-turned Republican Rep. Jeff Van Drew, R-N.J., told “Fox & Friends” on Monday that he wanted to thank President Trump for helping to shape the new Republican Party saying he thinks “the president broke everything open.”

value.title: Biden coronavirus adviser Dr. Zeke Emanuel once argued it's not worth living past 75
value.excerpt: Oncologist Dr. Zeke Emanuel, one of 10 advisory board members named to Democratic President-elect Joe Biden's coronavirus task force, argued in a 2014 essay that he doesn't want to live past 75.

value.title: Biden should support push for transparency in vote as ‘ultimate presidential act’: Turley
Seattle man fatally shot near Biden celebration rally: report
South Dakota Gov. Noem: Al Gore got his day in court -- Trump deserves the same consideration
value.excerpt: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem urged the country to “afford the 70.6 million Americans that voted for President Trump the same consideration" provided to former vice president Al Gore in the 2000 legal battle that resulted in a Supreme Court decision and a George W. Bush victory.

value.title: Trump campaign taps Rep. Doug Collins to lead recount team in Georgia
value.excerpt: The recount will begin as soon as canvassing has ended, the campaign said.

value.title: Trump campaign holds protest in Las Vegas to decry irregularities, claim ‘dead people,’ non-Nevadans voted
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign held a Sunday afternoon press conference outside the Clark County Elections Department in Las Vegas to denounce alleged irregularities in last week’s election.

value.title: 'Wonder Woman' star Lynda Carter celebrates Kamala Harris' win on 45th anniversary of the show
value.excerpt: Wonder Woman” actress Lynda Carter shared a congratulatory note to Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on a special day for fans of the superhero TV series.

value.title: Romney says Trump should 'follow every legal option he has,' but choose words 'carefully'
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, has no problem with President Trump challenging the 2020 election results in court, but said that he should tone down his public rhetoric.

value.title: Buttigieg: Republican Senate would go against 'will of the people' by opposing Biden agenda
value.excerpt: Biden transition team member Pete Buttigieg said Sunday that even if they win enough races to maintain control of the Senate, Republicans would be opposing the will of the American people if they stand in the way of President-elect Joe Biden's agenda.

value.title: Giuliani says Trump won't concede amid legal challenges
value.excerpt: President Trump wouldn’t concede the election at this point and the race is “far from over,” Rudy Guiliani said Saturday at a news conference in Philadelphia.

value.title: Message of Election 2020: Trump lost, but Trumpism did not
value.excerpt: In a typical election year, Biden would have carried other Democrats along with him. Instead, several promising Democratic Senate and House candidates, including incumbents, lost.

value.title: Biden and Harris to address supporters after winning election, ousting Trump
value.excerpt: President-elect Biden and Vice President-elect Harris will address supporters Saturday evening in Wilmington, Del., after earlier today claiming victory in the presidential election after the Fox News Decision Desk projected that they will defeat President Trump, denying him a second term.

value.title: Pro-Trump election Facebook group 'Stop the Steal' banned after calling for violence
value.excerpt: Facebook banned a pro-Trump group after posts suggesting "worrying calls for violence" surrounding the highly contentious results of the 2020 election.

value.title: Biden's inauguration during COVID-19: What the January event could look like
value.excerpt: Construction is already underway in Washington, D.C., in preparation for the presidential inauguration on Jan. 20, 2021. The date is set by the U.S. Constitution's 20th Amendment.

value.title: PHOTOS: After Biden declared president, crowds take to streets in NYC, Washington, DC
Rep. Jordan says Republicans picked up seats because voters don't like socialism, sees path for Trump
value.excerpt: Republicans picked up House seats despite projections that Democrats would have a "blue wave" on Election Day because "Americans don't like socialism," Rep. Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, told "Fox & Friends Weekend."

value.title: AOC wants anti-Trump Lincoln Project to give money to those who 'actually' made a difference
value.excerpt: After the Democratic Party failed to meet its electoral expectations in House races around the country on Election Day, one New York Democrat urged a conservative political group to donate money to progressive organizations.

value.title: Bernie Sanders thanks, praises progressives for 'Biden's victory' before race is called
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders thanked progressives Friday afternoon for aiding Democratic nominee Joe Biden’s 2020 presidential efforts – even with the race still too close to call.

value.title: Twitter marks 12 Trump tweets as 'misleading' in 60-hour span
value.excerpt: Twitter has marked at least a dozen tweets from President Trump as of Friday morning with a disclaimer that the tweets may contain "misleading" information about U.S. elections.

value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Trump 'likely' to run again in 2024 if he loses: Mick Mulvaney
value.excerpt: Trump's former acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney says the president isn't ready to bow out of politics.

value.title: Trump touts gains with minorities and women: 'We're the party of inclusion'
value.excerpt: President Trump touting his party’s gains with women and minorities, declared the Republican Party the “party of inclusion” in a news conference Thursday.
